      • preserveScale

        public final boolean preserveScale()
        Define whether the printed map will preserve the map scale or the map extent. Only one of these properties can be preserved to produce a high-resolution map for printing. If preserveScale is set to true, the map displayed in the print window will match the current scale of the map in the application. If preserveScale is false, the current extent of the map in the application displays in the printed map but the scale may change. The default value is true.
        Returns:
        boolean

      • setPreserveScale

        public final void setPreserveScale(boolean preserveScale)
        Set the preserveScale parameter.
        Parameters:
        preserveScale - - Define whether the printed map will preserve the map scale or the map extent. Only one of these properties can be preserved to produce a high-resolution map for printing. If preserveScale is set to true, the map displayed in the print window will match the current scale of the map in the application. If preserveScale is false, the current extent of the map in the application displays in the printed map but the scale may change. The default value is true.
